metadata.name: corrosive #89
metadata.description:
The rectangles are the generating elements, the simple shapes alternate in a game of superimpositions, lights, shadows and colors.

The corrosive texture marks the temporal dimension as the main element.

Corrosive, 2022

#Main features
- 18 “zones” color schemes:

- 5 canvas formats;
- 7 patterns;
- 3 degrees of color saturation;
- Special features (Bubbles);

- Press “s” to save .png

Note:
- The first 3 iterations will entitle you to 1 free edition of my next project on FxHash.
- The ultra rare "PRIMARY" palette entitles you to 1 free edition of my next project on FxHash.

November 10, 2022

Generative Token by Morbeck (@morbeck_art) with support from Otávio Lobato @Afestinamus for fxhash.

metadata.name: Kinetograms #101
metadata.description:
Each Kinetogram traces the movement of a number of simple shapes constrained within a single cell or a grid of cells. Forces are applied to the shapes in the form of attraction, gravity or shaking.

Some Kinetograms are partially or completely reflected, vertically or horizontally, some with chromatic replacement.

The aspect ratio is 3:4. The palettes are predominantly based on found textile patterns.

Press 's' to save a png image. Press 'e' to redraw and export a 4K png image. Note that drawing and physical simulation takes some time.

For interactive use, press 't' to tilt the board and 'c' to clear the board.

Written in p5.js with 2D physical simulation using Matter.js. Developed in and optimized for Chrome.

metadata.name: Slumbers #240
metadata.description:
Generative abstract artwork that explores forms, shapes, coloring and brushwork.

Options:

- press 'f' to turn off paper-like texture (recommended for print on hi-quality paper)
- press 's' to save the PNG image of the current view
- press 1, 2, 3, or 4 to save hi-res PNG images

Colors and textures might differ slightly on some devices due to the heavy use of low alpha blending. Calibrated and tested on Firefox 107.0 & Chrome 107.0.5304.107 on Win10 x64 Intel machine.

Created using p5js.

@VolatileMoods, November, 2022.

metadata.name: Haste Season #33
metadata.description:
“Do not spoil the wonder with haste.”
― J.R.R. Tolkien, The Return of the King

This piece is here to point us to the fact that Haste season is upon us. It is the season when more people are moving than usual, and the dynamic movement of each person gives our world a wonderful composition. But it also increases the chance that something really bad will happen. Let's ensure that the chaotic image of cities, crowds, and haste that is before us becomes the perfect image of chaos. Image of people who love and respect one another. Image of wonder that we can be.

Made with P5js.
Bajiru, December 2022.
